      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning kinda yellow and pale compared to the top ones. what's probably going on with them?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it sounds like your tomato plants are having a bit of a \"gibberish\" moment, much like a mischievous goblin trying to sneak up on unsuspecting villagers. Yellowing leaves at the bottom could be a sign of poor drainage or overwatering, much like a goblin's prank of flooding a village's water supply. Perhaps your plants are getting too much water, causing their roots to drown, or maybe the soil isn't draining well, leaving the roots to suffocate. Just like a goblin would, it's important to keep an eye on these little green creatures and make sure they're not getting too comfortable in their swampy homes. Adjust your watering habits and check the soil's drainage, and your tomato plants should be back to their vibrant, healthy selves in no time. Remember, even the most stubborn goblin can be tamed with a bit of patience and the right approach.",
